               <p>ROBERT BARWELL sworn.</p>
               <p>I <rs id="t17880402-28-viclabel137" type="occupation">keep the <placeName id="t17880402-28-crimeloc138">Red Hart, in Shoe-lane</placeName>
                     <interp inst="t17880402-28-crimeloc138" type="placeName" value="Red Hart, in Shoe-lane"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17880402-28-crimeloc138" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                     <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17880402-28-off135 t17880402-28-crimeloc138"></join>
                  </rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17880402-28-victim331 t17880402-28-viclabel137"></join>; I lost my pots on Tuesday last in the afternoon; the prisoner came in, and called for a penny worth of Hock; he drank that, and called for another penny-worth; he then went backwards and came into the tap-room, and paid for both, and went back again; I followed him, and found my property upon him; I took him into custody, and he delivered the pots up to me; my name is upon them.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I was drunk; I leave it to the mercy of the Court.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17880402-28-person332">
